<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks With Iraq Begin; Expansion of Ties Sought </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1902110994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1902110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad has called for the expansion of ties with 
Tehran. During the first round of talks between Iraqi 
Undersecretary for Foreign Affairs Mr. Sa'd 'Abd-al-Majid 
al-Faysal and our country's deputy foreign minister for 
international affairs, the Iraqi undersecretary placed emphasis 
on the expansion of the two countries' relations. 
  During the talks, held in Tehran this morning, the two sides 
also stressed the way should be paved for the creation of mutual 
trust, aimed at the expansion of ties. They also called for the 
resolution of the outstanding problems. 

</TEXT>

