<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Meeting With Kenya's Moi Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1802161194 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 0430 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1802161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih has 
announced the postponement of the meeting between President 
Lieutenant General 'Umar al-Bashir and Kenyan President Daniel 
arap Moi, at the request of the Kenyan side. He told SUNA [as 
received] that an envoy of Lieutenant General 'Umar al-Bashir 
would leave for Nairobi to look into the reasons for the 
postponement and to confirm Sudan's firm stance towards the 
Intergovernmental Authority on Drought and Development [IGADD] 
initiative, as characterized by Sudan's unreserved backing for 
the initiative. The envoy would explain that Sudan regarded 
IGADD as a neighborly group, close to itself, aware of 
conditions in Sudan and which enjoys life [as heard] for the 
sake of a peaceful solution. He added that his visit had also 
been postponed at the request of the Kenyan Foreign Ministry. 
  His excellency added that the Kenyan ambassador to Sudan had 
left Sudan for home yesterday after meetings with Sudanese 
officials in Sudan. He had taken with him the Sudanese 
Government's request that the IGADD states persevere in their 
efforts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

