<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's al-Bid Arrives in Damascus, Makes Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1902134794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1215 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1902134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the Presidential 
Council in the Republic of Yemen arrived in Damascus at noon 
today. 
  Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam led those who received 
al-Bid at the Damascus International Airport. Khaddam and 
al-Bid then headed in an official motorcade for the guest 
palace, al-Bid's residence. 
  Al-Bid made a statement to the correspondent of the Syrian 
Arab News Agency in which he said: 
  "We are glad, while visiting the sisterly Syrian Arab 
Republic, to meet with our brothers in this fraternal country, 
led by President Hafiz al-Asad, to discuss fraternal bilateral 
relations and ways of bolstering and developing them, in 
addition to the Arab and international situation. 
  "It is an opportunity to acquaint our Syrian brothers with 
developments in Yemen and the results of national dialogue and 
efforts contained in the document of pledge and accord that will 
be signed in the Jordanian capital, Amman, on the 10th of the 
blessed Ramadan. 
  "We believe that it is an opportunity to discuss with our 
brothers in the beloved Syria the means of healing the rift, 
restoring Arab cohesion, and organizing the single Arab house in 
a manner that will contribute to the restoration of Arab 
solidarity and the activation of the Arab nation's role among 
the nations. This will come in the wake of new international 
circumstances and changes, and in a manner that allows the Arab 
nation to confront the dangers and challenges facing it. 
  "On this occasion, I am pleased to express my satisfaction 
with the development of fraternal relations between our country 
and the sisterly Syrian Arab Republic, and to emphasize the 
importance of developing these relations in a manner that serves 
the joint interests of the two fraternal Yemeni and Syrian 
peoples, and the issues that concern our Arab and Islamic 
nations, and strengthens the role and status of the two 
countries in the Arab and international arenas." 
  Al-Bid is accompanied by Dr. Yasin Sa'id Nu'man, a Yemeni 
Socialist Party Political Bureau member and head of the 
secretariat of the party's Central Committee. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

