<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   King Hosts Yemeni Accord Signing Ceremony </TI></H3>
<H4>   Yemeni House Speaker Gives Address </H4>
<F P=102> JN2002190794 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1524 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2002190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Remarks by 'Abdallah al-Ahmar, speaker of the Yemeni House </F>
of Representatives and leader of the Yemeni Reform Grouping, 
following the signing of the Yemeni document of pledge and 
accord on 20 February at the Royal Hashemite Court in Amman -- 
live] 
  [Text] In the name of God, the compassionate, the 
merciful. On my own behalf, and in my capacity as the leader of 
the third party in the government coalition, I am pleased to 
thank His Majesty King Husayn for hosting this blessed gathering 
and this agreement. God willing, this will end the dispute and 
the crisis. It will enable all officials to return to their 
posts, so we can start working to implement this document and 
our government and parties' programs, so we can serve our 
country and free it from the economic and political crisis it 
is experiencing. 
  We hope this gathering of ours will end the crisis and allow 
us to enter into a new age, the age of building, work, and 
cooperation, and loyalty to our dear homeland. 
  Finally, I once again thank his majesty for hosting this 
agreement and for his efforts. God's blessings be upon you. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

