<H3> <TI>   King Hosts Yemeni Accord Signing Ceremony </TI></H3>
<H4>   Jordan-Yemen Contacts Reported </H4>
<F P=102> JN2002193194 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2002193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Kassab Samawi] </F>
  [Text] Before the signing of the document of pledge and 
accord by the Yemeni political dialogue parties, the Royal 
Hashemite Court witnessed a series of contacts between His 
Majesty King Husayn, the Yemeni leaders, and Jordan's guests who 
were invited to bless this agreement. 
  His Majesty King Husayn received 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice 
chairman of the Yemeni Presidential Council. The meeting was 
attended by His Highness Crown Prince Hasan. The meeting, which 
lasted for some time, was also attended by Yasin Nu'man, head of 
the secretariat of the Yemeni Socialist Party's Central 
Committee. 
  His Majesty King Husayn also conferred at Raghadan Palace 
this afternoon with His Excellency 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Yemeni 
president; Yasir 'Arafat, president of the state of Palestine; 
'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the Yemeni Presidential 
Council; Shaykh 'Abdallah al-Ahmar, head of the Yemeni Reform 
Grouping; Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid, Arab League's secretary 
General; and Yusuf Bin-'Alawi, the Sultanate of Oman's minister 
of state for foreign affairs, before they all headed for the 
throne hall at Raghadan Palace. 
  During that meeting, maintaining Yemeni national unity and 
the ability of the Arab nation to overcome its difficulties and 
resolve its problems within the Arab framework were emphasized. 
The guests highly appreciated Jordan's role in closing Arab 
ranks and building solidarity on the basis of confidence, 
cooperation, and brotherhood. 
  Following the signing of the historic document, His Majesty 
King Husayn held a fast-breaking banquet at Basman Palace in 
honor of the Yemeni leaders and the guests. 
  The banquet was attended by His Highness Crown Prince Hasan 
and top government officials, as well as civil and military 
officials. 

</TEXT>

