<H3> <TI>   King Hosts Yemeni Accord Signing Ceremony </TI></H3>
<H4>   King Attends Post-Ceremony Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> JN2102080194 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0500 GMT 
21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2102080194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn patronized a meeting at the 
al-Hashimiyah Palace yesterday evening attended by 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Yemeni Presidential Council; 
his deputy 'Ali Salim al-Bid; and leaders of the Yemeni 
political forces and parties. 
  In his name and on behalf of all Jordanians, his majesty 
welcomed the brother members of the Yemeni leadership and 
expressed his appreciation to this leadership and to all the 
Yemeni political forces for their historic achievement 
represented by the document of pledge and accord. This accord 
is a good beginning for fraternal Yemen and the entire nation, 
God willing, the king added. 
  During the meeting, the conferees reviewed ways to implement 
the document of pledge and accord which was signed yesterday 
evening by all Yemeni forces, organs, and institutions in order 
to enhance the unionist and democratic march of sisterly Yemen. 
  Attending the meeting on the Jordanian side were His 
Highness 
Crown Prince Hasan; Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali; 
His Excellency al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, chief of the Royal 
Hashemite Court; Marwan al-Qasim, his majesty's political 
adviser; Dr. Khalid al-Karaki, his majesty's adviser; and the 
Jordanian ambassador to Yemen. 
  Representing the Yemeni side at the meeting were 
'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani, Presidential Council member; Salim 
Salih, Presidential Council member; Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, 
the prime minister; Mujahid Abu-Shawarib, deputy prime minister; 
Sinan Abu- Luhum, head of the National Forces Union; 
'Abd-al-Wahhab al-Anisi, secretary of the Yemeni Reform 
Grouping; Dr. Yasin Nu'man, head of the secretariat office of 
the Yemeni Socialist Party's Central Committee; 'Abd-al-Karim 
al-Iryani, minister of planning and development; and Jarallah 
'Umar, minister of culture and tourism. 

</TEXT>

