<H4>   Salih Makes Pre-Departure Statement </H4>
<F P=102> JN2102163994 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 
21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2102163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] His Excellency President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Yemeni Presidential Council, left Amman for home 
this afternoon after taking part in the signing of the Yemeni 
accord document in Amman yesterday under the patronage of His 
Majesty King Husayn. [passage omitted] 
  In a statement to the JORDANIAN NEWS AGENCY, President Salih 
thanked the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan, represented by His 
Majesty King Husayn, for hosting the signing of the accord 
document. He said: On the sidelines of the occasion, we held 
consultations on issues of interest to the Republic of Yemen and 
the Hashmemite Kingdom of Jordan, and we discussed several 
issues pertaining to our Arab and Islamic nation--issues on 
which both countries maintain identical positions and views. 
  Although we have overcome the challenges of the crisis in 
our 
Yemeni homeland, we, as Arabs, still face more general and more 
comprehensive challenges, which we should confront seriously and 
honestly. This will not take place unless we patch up our 
differences and consider higher national interests above other, 
narrower regional interests. These other interests are 
distracting our countries' attention from promoting collective 
pan-Arab action and formulating the situation in accordance with 
a responsible desire to restore and enhance Arab solidarity. We 
must do this in order to meet the minimum aspirations of our 
peoples at this time, a time in which we see a new trend of 
regional relations that conflicts with the collective action for 
which we yearn. 

</TEXT>

