<H4>   Further on Salih's Statement </H4>
<F P=102> JN2102174694 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1700 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2102174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih has left Amman 
after he took part in signing the Yemeni reconciliation and 
reform accord. His majesty the king and His Royal Highness 
Crown Prince Hasan led a farewell ceremony to President Salih at 
the airport. The prime minister, the speakers of Upper and Lower 
Houses of Parliament, and his majesty the king's advisers also 
took part in the farewell ceremony. 
  In a departure statement, President Salih paid tribute to 
efforts exerted by his majesty in ending the rift in Yemen. He 
expressed his thanks to those who worked and planned for the 
signing ceremony. President Salih said he discussed during his 
stay bilateral issues of concern and other pan-Arab and Muslim 
issues. 
  The Yemeni president said more challenges are facing Arabs 
that need firmness and faithfulness. He said this would be 
achieved by reconciliation among Arabs and putting pan-Arab 
interests before regional ones. Mr. Salih said that he is 
looking for bilateral Arab meetings as a first step toward 
gatherings that would be of greater benefit for all Arabs. 

</TEXT>

