<F P=103> NC1902130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Feb (MENA)--A ranking Libyan diplomatic 
source in Cairo has denied that Libya is any way connected to 
the assassination of Jordanian diplomat Na'ib al-Ma'aytah in 
Lebanon recently. 
  The source said in statements today that Libya condemns 
terrorism in all its forms and that it has cut off all relations 
with any groups that follow a course of violence instead of 
dialogue and peaceful negotiations. He denied the presence of 
Abu-Nidal's [Sabri al-Banna] group on Libyan territory. He also 
denied that any Libyan officials had met with any members or 
leaders belonging to Abu-Nidal's group recently. 
  The Libyan source believes that raising Libya's name in 
relation to the assassination of the Jordanian diplomat, as some 
newspaper reports have done, is an attempt to sour 
Jordanian-Libyan relations, especially during this phase of 
peace. He stressed Libya's interest in its relations with 
Lebanon. 

