<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Discusses Measures To Fight Terrorism </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2202083294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2202083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] In a meeting presided over by Prime Minister Dr. 
'Atif Sidqi last night, the Cabinet discussed a program for 
national action during the current stage that includes an 
integrated strategy for all fields of action, Information 
Minister Safwat al-Sharif said at the end of the meeting. 
  During the special session, Dr. Sidqi noted that elements of 
stability in Egypt strengthen its ability to play a pivotal role 
in the region and the world. He pointed out that the phenomenon 
of terrorism does not affect Egypt's political or economic 
progress, and the people of Egypt, with their culture and 
tenacity, will continue the march of development and progress 
and face all challenges with complete confidence in a bright and 
stable future. [passage omitted] 
  The Cabinet also discussed a program for international 
cooperation to fight terrorism. The program includes a report 
prepared by the Cabinet expressing appreciation for the positive 
role played by several countries in providing important 
information for coordinating the fight against terrorism. The 
report notes the need to extend bridges of cooperation with more 
countries to collectively confront terrorist organizations, 
expedite the conclusion of cooperation agreements with a number 
of countries on combating terrorism, and regularly supply 
countries with the facts about terrorist practices and the 
popular reaction to these crimes. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

