Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Feb (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
today met with Israeli Ambassador David Sultan. 
  Following the meeting, the Israeli ambassador said that they 
discussed the current developments in the peace talks and the 
efforts being made to give impetus to the peace process. He 
added that the Palestinian and Israeli delegations will resume 
their meetings in Cairo tomorrow, Monday, and that the Israeli 
delegation led by Major General Amnon Shahaq will arrived in 
Cairo tomorrow. 
  In reply to a question on Palestinian president Yasir 
'Arafat's accusations that Israel is not carrying out its 
commitments, the Israeli ambassador said that Israel is 
committed to all its pledges and hopes that the two sides will 
reach agreement. He added that the important thing is resuming 
the Palestinian-Israeli talks and reaching an agreement as soon 
as possible on the implementation of the Declaration of 
Principles, especially as the two sides made progress in the 
negotiations held in Taba last week. 

