<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calls for Total Withdrawal From Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2102151794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1422 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2102151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Feb (MENA)--Commenting on reports that the 
Serbs have begun withdrawing their heavy weapons from around 
Sarajevo, Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa said today that the 
beginning of the implementation of this withdrawal must lead to 
total withdrawal so that we will be assured that no other 
aggression will take place against Sarajevo. 
  Musa said if the work to lift the siege of Sarajevo 
succeeds, 
it is necessary and desirable that this also be done at other 
besieged towns. Thus, several aspects of Serb aggression can be 
dealt with and a settlement process can begin in a better 
atmosphere. 
  Musa added that Egypt is closely watching the situation. It 
will continue its contacts with the states concerned. He 
explained that Egypt is maintaining contacts with the European 
states. It is also maintaining contact with the Islamic state 
[Bosnia Herzegovina] within the context of the Islamic 
Conference Organization's interest in this issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

