<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Confirms Landing of Iranian Helicopter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202085194 Tehran IRNA in English 0732 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202085194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 22, IRNA -- A spokesman for Iran's 
Foreign Ministry here Tuesday confirmed the emergency landing of 
a missing Iranian helicopter in northern Iraq. The spokesman 
called on the Iraqi Government to furnish Iran with further 
details on the issue through diplomatic channels. 
  The helicopter with two crew members on board was 
disappeared 
three days ago. The pilot in his last contact had reported 
technical failure. The spokesman said he is unable to precisely 
comment on the cause of the emergency landing due to the 
contradictory reports reaching here. 
  According to reports reaching here from the western border 
city of Sanandaj a large number of helicopters conduct flights 
over the region to transport relief aids and maintain security 
in the border region. The authorities in Kordestan Province 
had originally thought that the helicopter had crashed in the 
mountains in northeast of Iran. Informed sources in Kordestan 
said that reports coming from northern Iraq on the whereabouts 
of the helicopter and the fate of its crew are not highly 
reliable. 

</TEXT>

