<F P=102>  AB2002190094 Khartoum SUNA in English 1740 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2002190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 20 Feb -- A political source described the 
visit of the U.S. ambassador to the Sudan, Donald Nerson [name 
as received] to some areas in the south of the Sudan without 
permission from the Sudanese Government as the violation of the 
national sovereignty of the country and that the U.S. ambassador 
in Khartoum misused of his responsibility and we do not keep 
silence on this regard [sentence as received]. 
  The source said in a statement to SUNA that this act came in 
the context of the open alignment to the rebel movement by the 
United States. 
  The source added that the U.S. ambassador act came in the 
framework of securing the arrival of the war equipments to the 
rebel movement saying that it is a desperate attempt to raise 
the spiritual moral of the rebel forces. 

