<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   King Hosts Yemeni Accord Signing Ceremony </TI></H3>
<H4>   Yemeni President Speaks </H4>
<F P=102> JN2002164994 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1515 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2002164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Remarks by Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih following </F>
the signing of the Yemeni document of pledge and accord on 20 
February at the Royal Hashemite Court in Amman -- live] 
  [Text] In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
  My brother, His Majesty King Husayn Bin-Talal; brother 
struggler Yasir 'Arafat, president of the state of Palestine; 
brother leaders of sisterly Jordan; their excellencies the heads 
of Arab and foreign diplomatic missions: Allow me in the name 
of the steadfast Yemeni people to lavishly thank my dear brother 
His Majesty King Husayn Bin-Talal [applause], who exerted great 
efforts, along with his government and people and all the good 
in the Arab homeland, led, too, by my brother struggler Yasir 
'Arafat [applause] and many sisterly and friendly states, 
including the United States of America and the EEC and others in 
the world, who were concerned about Yemeni unity, which was 
proclaimed on 22 May 1990 in a peaceful and democratic way. 
  God be praised, we are here in sisterly Jordan to sign the 
document of pledge and accord drafted by the Political Forces 
Dialogue Committee of national parties and independent 
personalities. We -- the leadership, the government, and the 
people, led by the three coalition parties, the General People's 
Congress, the Yemeni Socialist Party, and the Yemeni Reform 
Grouping and the rest of the political forces -- hope that with 
this signing we will really move on to practical implementation, 
as stated in the document of pledge and accord. 
  Your majesty, we highly appreciate your hosting of this 
large 
gathering of social and political personalities, national 
figures, and historic leaders, led by brother Field Marshal 
'Abdallah al-Sallal, brother 'Ali Nasir Muhammad, brother 
'Abd-al-Rahman al-Baydani, and many other national figures and 
historic Yemeni leaders. Our father, great struggler 
'Abd-al-Rahman Bin-Yahya al- Iryani, was supposed to be with us, 
but he was delayed in Damascus for some reason. We thank you in 
the name of these forces and in the name of your people and 
brothers in Yemen for your eagerness to maintain Yemeni unity. 
  God willing, we will not disappoint you or our people in 
Jordan and the entire good Arab nation, which is concerned about 
the Yemeni unity. We will measure up to the good opinion of 
all. We will break with all past pages, in all their forms, 
tragedies, rivalries, and problems. We make the promise of 
loyal men that with this document we will move to the stage of 
pledge, success, and implementation, God willing. From the 
bottom of my heart and in the name of these leaders, I once 
again thank you very much. God's peace and blessings be upon 
you. [applause] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

