Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Serious differences of opinion erupted today in the 
Cairo security talks. An Israeli delegate said today that the 
gaps in the positions of the sides are unbridgeable and that yet 
another meeting between Peres and 'Arafat will be needed. Our 
correspondent Roni Daniyel has learned that Israel rejected the 
PLO's demand to release all 9,000 Palestinian prisoners. 
  In the Civilian Affairs Committee, on the other hand, 
significant progress has been reported in most issues. 

