<H3> <TI>   Minister on `Real Difficulties' in Economic Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2202153894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 22 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2202153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Referring to the economic 
talks with the Palestinians in Paris, Finance Minister Avraham 
Shohat said they have run into real difficulties owing to the 
fact that the PLO delegates presented new positions which are 
incompatible with the understandings reached in the previous 
rounds of negotiations. In his meeting with Abu-al-'Ala' [Ahmad 
Quray'] tomorrow, Shohat said, he will seek to clarify whether 
the PLO officially changed its positions. 
  Minister Shohat believes a change of policy may be needed, 
and instead of open economies, a decision will be made to close 
the economies of Israel and the autonomy to each other. 

