<H3> <TI>   Newspaper Strike Ends; Dailies To Reappear </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202230794 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202230794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Numerous national newspapers, which disappeared 
from the newsstands due to the strike at the central Algiers 
printing company, will start reappearing beginning this evening 
because this strike has come to an end. [passage omitted] 
  The employees of the Central Algiers Printing Company have 
been on an open strike since yesterday. This was due to a 
disagreement with management regarding the review of the salary 
grid and the implementation of the collective agreement. 
  This strike had a quick effect, which resulted in the 
dailies 
EL MASA and LE SOIR D'ALGERIE not being published since 
yesterday evening and the absence of about seven national 
dailies from the newsstands today. [passage omitted] 

