<H3> <TI>   Other Criminals Captured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2202222194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2131 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2202222194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 22 Feb (MENA)--Extensive security campaigns 
during the past 24 hours in the slum districts organized by 
al-Jizah security department have resulted in arresting around 
700 people who are suspected of various political and criminal 
violations. 
  Brigadier General Sayyid Farid, director of the General 
Department for al-Jizah Investigations, said that the storming 
of the slum areas also resulted in the arrest of 145 fugitive 
extremists from Upper Egypt. The security forces also seized a 
number of firearms, including three machine guns. 
  He said that within the framework of instructions from 
Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi on the need to extensively 
search for activists, during this campaign, in which most of the 
security organs participated, the security forces succeeded in 
resolving many cases, including 15 drug cases of various kinds, 
and in shutting down numerous drug dens. 
  The search forces -- led by Brigadier General 'Abd-al-Wahhab 
Khalil, head of the Investigations Department -- succeeded in 
arresting 48 fugitives who were fleeing various sentences for 
crimes they had committed. They also arrested a number of gangs 
specializing in robbing houses and stores in all parts of 
al-Jizah. 
  The director of the General Department for Investigations 
noted that the defendants confessed to their crimes and have 
been referred to the prosecution for interrogation and 
investigation. 

</TEXT>

