<H3> <TI>   Clashes Reported Between North, South; Reaction Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Incident Said `Contained' </H4>
<F P=102> JN2102175494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1710 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2102175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Ministry of Defense and 
the General Staff of the Armed Forces has informed the Yemeni 
News Agency, SABA' that the regrettable military incident that 
took place in Abyan Governorate was contained this morning. The 
source added: Once Presidential Council Chairman brother 
Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, and Presidential 
Council Vice Chairman brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid were informed of 
this incident, they instructed that the incident be contained, 
that a rapid investigation of the circumstances surrounding it 
be conducted, and that full compliance with instructions be 
enforced. 
  The Military Committee has been asked to monitor the 
implementation of the instructions, and to take the necessary 
relevant measures. 
  The source asserted that this incident will not undermine 
the 
joy that has swept our people in the aftermath of the signing of 
the accord document in Arab Amman, the city of accord and 
reconciliation, under the sponsorship of His Majesty King Husayn 
Bin-Talal and the Jordanian people. Moreover, this incident 
will not deter all from continuing to mobilize efforts to 
implement the document of accord in order to build a modern 
Yemeni state, a state of institutions, law, and order, the 
source concluded. 

</TEXT>

