<H3> <TI>   Clashes Reported Between North, South; Reaction Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Sources: Situation `Close' to `Exploding' </H4>
<F P=102> JN2202162394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1600 GMT 22 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2202162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sources close to Defense Minister Haytham Qasim 
Tahir said in Aden today that the military situation in the 
southern Abyan region, where armed clashes took place between 
northern and southern units on 21 February, is close to the 
point of exploding. The same sources said that the country is 
now in an undeclared state of war. 
  The tension follows the signing of an accord agreement last 
Sunday. The agreement aims to end the political crisis that has 
been plaguing the country since last August. 

</TEXT>

