<H3> <TI>   Announcement Made Concerning Basil al-Asad's Duties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2202143594 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 22 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2202143594 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Damascus -- A prominent Syrian figure yesterday 
said in an official, open, and clear manner that Dr. Bashshar 
al-Asad, President Hafiz al-Asad's second eldest son, will 
assume the duties which used to be carried out by his brother 
Staff Major Basil al-Asad, who was killed in a car crash last 
month. 
  This announcement came in a lecture delivered by Dr. Bahjat 
Sulayman, a senior and influential political figure very close 
to President Hafiz al-Asad. He said: The masses in Syria see 
in Dr. Bashshar al-Asad a guarantee and a symbol needed for the 
continuation and stability of Hafiz al-Asad's line. [passage 
omitted] 
  There have been numerous indications since Basil al-Asad's 
death that Dr. Bashshar al-Asad is going to carry the leadership 
banner and continue the big aspirations launched by his brother, 
Basil. 
  Dr. Bashshar al-Asad is an ophthalmologist who was preparing 
to specialize in a European state when he heard the news of his 
brother Basil's death. 

</TEXT>

