<H3> <TI>   Al-Hirawi, al-Asad Discuss Peace, Other Issues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Coordination Needs Discussed </H4>
<F P=102> NC2002193494 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 20 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2002193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Summit talks between Presidents Ilyas al-Hirawi and 
Hafiz al-Asad are still under way. According to our Damascus 
correspondent, the two presidents met for three and a half hours 
today. Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam attended part of 
the talks. 
  Our correspondent cites sources close to the talks as saying 
that the two presidents discussed Lebanese-Israeli talks, the 
conditions made by Israel, and Israel's position concerning UN 
Security Council Resolution 425. The Lebanese and Syrian 
presidents also reviewed U.S. views concerning Lebanese-Israeli 
talks and the U.S. message to Lebanon, which warns of the 
repercussions of the volatile situation in the south. Al-Hirawi 
and al-Asad stressed the need for coordination between their 
countries in matters of domestic, foreign, diplomatic, and 
security policy. 
  The two presidents met again this afternoon. Sources close 
to the talks say that various domestic issues will be discussed 
in that session. 

</TEXT>

