<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel Reportedly Annexes `Vast Areas' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2202212494 Beirut AL-'AHD in Arabic 11 Feb 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> NC2202212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-'AHD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Security information from inside the occupied strip 
reports that the Zionist occupation forces recently sliced off 
vast areas of Lebanese territory in the hills of Saddanah which 
lie alongside al-Majidiyah farm at the southwestern corner of 
the Golan Heights and annexed them to the occupied territories. 
  Citing eyewitnesses, the reports said that the Israelis have 
built asphalt roads through the al-Malikiyah gateway, which they 
set up in 1948, to these hills, which they now have linked to 
the farms in Shab'a. They occupied the latter in 1967. The 
reports add that the occupation forces set up many camps and 
observation posts in these heights and surrounded them with 
barbed wire. In addition, they set up iron pillars, flood 
lights, and other military equipment. They also imposed a 
curfew under the pretext that these are military areas. It is 
worth noting here that the Israelis established many settlements 
among the farms of Shab'a and built roads linking them to the 
Tiberias area many years ago. 

</TEXT>

