Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lebanese judiciary is eager to handle the murder 
of the Jordanian diplomat Na'ib 'Umran al-Ma'ayitah with extreme 
delicacy and secure the defense for those charged with the 
murder, who belong to the Abu-Nidal-led Fatah Movement--the 
Revolutionary Council [FRC]. The defendants are interrogated in 
the presence of Bisharah Abu-Sa'd, a lawyer who is a partner and 
the brother-in-law of Deputy Najah Wakim. 
  AL-SHIRA' previously reported that the Abu-Nidal group 
undertakes the personal protection of Deputy Wakim by providing 
him with a permanent escort of armed men. Hence, Wakim adheres 
to the FRC line and adopts it in his political positions. 

