<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Killed in Sidon for `Moral Reasons' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2302120994 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1115 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2302120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Sidon today, Palestinian Muhammad Sa'id al-Sayigh 
was killed and his daughters Ruwaydah and Rana wounded when 
explosives placed under the driver's seat in his Toyota went 
off. There was an estimated half a kg of explosives. 
  Our correspondent learned that the crime was committed for 
moral reasons and that the deceased had distributed pornographic 
films that prompted opposition from Islamic groups in Sidon. 

</TEXT>

