<F P=102>  PM2202151594 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 22 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2202151594 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- 'Udayy Saddam Husayn 
assumed the task of running the affairs of the Iraqi Industry 
Ministry 10 days ago, namely when Minister Husayn Kamil 
al-Majid's condition began to deteriorate and as a result he was 
moved to Amman to undergo surgery to remove a brain tumor. 
  Sources said that the Iraqi president has authorized his 
eldest son to temporarily assume the task of running the 
establishments which used to be run by al-Majid, Saddam's 
son-in-law. 

