<H3> <TI>   Saddam Decorates Ba'th Party, RCC Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2202202694 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1700 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2202202694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn, may God preserve 
him, has decorated 'Izzat Ibrahim, vice chairman of the 
Revolution Command Council [RCC], Arab Socialist Ba'th Party 
National Command members, RCC members, and members of the Iraq 
Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party with the medal of high 
merit for their distinguished role in the Mother of Battles. 
  Leader President Saddam Husayn, may God support him, 
congratulated the honorees and beseeched Almighty God to protect 
them, along with all our people, and lead their steps on the 
road of firm principles to serve our beloved homeland. 
  Hatim Hamdan al-'Azzawi, chief of the Presidential Office, 
attended the awarding ceremony. Following are the texts of the 
presidential decrees: 
  In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
  Presidential Decree: 
  In view of RCC Vice Chairman 'Izzat Ibrahim Khalil's stand 
during the Mother of Battles, and based on the provisions of RCC 
Decree No. 407, dated 17 November 1991, we decree the following: 
  RCC Vice Chairman 'Izzat Ibrahim Khalil shall be awarded the 
medal of high merit. 
  The competent ministers shall implement this decree. 
  [Signed] Saddam Husayn, president of the Republic 
  In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
  Presidential Decree: 
  In view of the stand adopted by the Arab Socialist Ba'th 
Party National Command members, whose names are listed below, 
during the Mother of Battles, and based on the provisions of RCC 
Decree No. 407, dated 17 November 1991, we decree the following: 
  The Arab Socialist Ba'th Party National Command members, 
whose names are listed below, shall be awarded the medal of high 
merit: 
  'Abd-al-Majid al-Tayyib al-Rafi'i 
  Badr-al-Din Muddaththir Sulayman 
  Ilyas Nakhlah Farah 
  The competent ministers shall implement this decree. 
  [Signed] Saddam Husayn, president of the Republic 
  In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
  Presidential Decree: 
  In view of the stand adopted by the RCC members, whose names 
are listed below, during the Mother of Battles, and based on the 
provisions of RCC Decree No. 407, dated 17 November 1991, we 
decree the following: 
  The RCC members, whose names are listed below, shall be 
awarded the medal of high merit: 
  Taha Yasin Ramadan 
  Tariq 'Aziz 
  Taha Muhyi-al-Din Ma'ruf 
  'Ali Hasan al-Majid 
  Muhammad Hamzah al-Zubaydi 
  Mizban Khadr Hadi 
  The competent ministers shall implement this decree. 
  [Signed] Saddam Husayn, president of the Republic 
  In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
  Presidential Decree: 
  In view of the stand adopted by members of the Iraq Command 
of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party, whose names are listed below, 
during the Mother of Battles, and based on the provisions of RCC 
Decree No. 407, dated 17 November 1991, we decree the following: 
  Members of the Iraq Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'th 
Party, whose names are listed below, shall be awarded the medal 
of high merit: 
