<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leader Says Time `Appropriate' Time for Rushdie Sentence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202140694 Tehran IRNA in English 1314 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 22, IRNA -- Head of the 15th of Khordad 
Foundation (which has set a prize for Salman Rushdie's head), 
Ayatollah Hasan Sane'i believes that the time is now appropriate 
to carry out the death sentence against the apostate author of 
'The Satanic Verses.' 
  The morning daily `JOMHURI-YE ESLAMI' quoted Ayatollah 
Sane'i 
as saying that five years after the death verdict was issued 
against the Indian-born British author, the world Muslims now 
fully realised the matter. 
  The desperate attempts of Rushdie and his western backers 
too 
have only failed to lift the verdict and have only added to 
Muslims' wrath. 'Today the situation is appropriate more than 
any other time for the execution of Salman Rushdie,' the 
ayatollah stressed. 
  Ayatollah Sane'i underlined that the Islamic countries 
solidarity as well as the Organization of Islamic Conference's 
(OIC) renewed support for the verdict against Rushdie as factors 
paving the way to carry out the death decree. 
  According to western media, the ayatollah said, Rushdie was 
gradually dying and even the police protection failed to improve 
his morale. 'It is the fate of anyone who insults Prophet 
Muhammad (PBUH) and over one billion Muslims' sanctities.' 
  Referring to formation of some European committees to 
support 
the apostate writer, the ayatollah said their act too was an 
insult to the sanctities of Muslims. 

</TEXT>

