<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mirsalim Appointment Favored </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202120394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] After President 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani's speech and since there were no deputies who 
had registered their names to speak against Mr. Mirsalim's 
ministerial appointment, three deputies spoke in favor of his 
appointment. They pointed to the sensitive nature of the 
current situation and the importance of the Ministry of Culture 
and Islamic guidance's responsibilities. They considered that 
Mr. Mirsalim was qualified for the post. 
  Next, Mr. Mostafa Mirsalim, minister of culture and Islamic 
guidance, explained the main points of his programs aimed at 
achieving the cultural objectives of the revolution. He 
described the extensive dimensions of the western cultural 
onslaught against Islamic culture. He said: In confronting such 
an onslaught, we should safeguard our indigenous culture and 
Islamic values with all our being. He emphasized: The most 
important factor in spiritual growth is to raise the cultural 
level of the public and this is a priority and an essential part 
of our work. All programs should be formulated and supplied 
within the framework of Islamic values. 
  The minister of culture and Islamic guidance said that the 
lack of clear opinions based on religious jurisprudence that 
could resolve certain matters concerning the art world, the 
unequal distribution of art facilities in the country, and also 
the question of training and retraining of specialized and 
effective managers for the cultural and art sectors of the 
country, are among existing bottlenecks. He hoped that through 
the efforts of relevant officials, these bottlenecks will be 
removed as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

