<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trial of KEYHAN-E HAVA'I Managing Director Begins </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94LA0080C Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 26 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0080C </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Tehran, 27 Dey [17 Jan] (KEYHAN News Service) -- In 
the continued investigation of the complaint from 'Ali Akbar 
Sa'idi-Sirjani about the publication of an article criticizing 
his views in the publication KEYHAN-E HAVA'I, the trial of 
KEYHAN-E HAVA'I's managing director will begin this year in the 
month of Esfand [20 February-19 March 1994] at the Tehran Public 
Prosecutor's Office. 
  According to the summons issued by the Ministry of Justice 
Palace on 5 Dey [26 December] for 'Abbas Salimi-Namin, managing 
director of KEYHAN-E HAVA'I, the trial is scheduled for 1000 on 
8 Esfand [27 February] this year at Tehran Penal Court 2, Branch 
199. 
  In this summons, the charge against the managing director of 
KEYHAN-E HAVA'I is said to be "publishing lies." 
  Sa'idi-Sirjani began his complaint against KEYHAN-E HAVA'I's 
managing director in the year 1368 [21 March 1989-20 March 
1990], when an article criticizing his writing in the newspaper 
ETTELA'AT was published in KEYHAN-E HAVA'I. Investigation of 
this case was begun in earnest at that time by the Ministry of 
Justice. The managing director of KEYHAN-E HAVA'I has been 
summoned several times to give explanations to the public 
prosecutor, and according to the most recent summons, his trial 
is to begin in the month of Esfand. 
  After questioning the managing director of KEYHAN-E HAVA'I 
and listening to his explanations, the special investigator for 
this case determined that Sa'idi-Sirjani's claim could not be 
pursued and announced that the investigation of the case was 
closed, but the Tehran deputy prosecutor canceled the 
investigator's opinion and reopened the case. 
  Sa'idi-Sirjani is among those who are interviewed on foreign 
radio programs such as the BBC and the Voice of America, usually 
about cultural, social, and sometimes political matters, and his 
writing is published in Persian-language newspapers published 
abroad. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-35315 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes036_s_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-036 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

