<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   New IRI School Opens in Damascus </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94LA0080E Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 22 Dec 93 p 20 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0080E </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Tehran, 22 Azar [15 Dec] (KEYHAN-E HAVA'I News 
Service) -- A new Iranian school has opened in Damascus, 
admitting Iranian, Afghan, Pakistani, and Arab students. 
  This school was opened on Woman's Day in Damascus near the 
grave of Her Holiness Zaynab (peace be upon her) on the birth 
anniversary of Her Holiness Fatimeh Zahra (peace be upon her) 
through the efforts of officials of the Islamic Republic of 
Iran's Ministry of Education and Training and the office 
supervising Iranian schools outside the country in Syria and 
Lebanon. 
  At the opening ceremonies for this school, the supervisor of 
Iranian schools outside the country said: The establishment of 
these schools is an important step in the spread of the real 
Islamic culture, and participation in these schools by friends 
of the Islamic Republic of Iran increases every day. 
  Studying in the new school are 130 Iranian, Afghan and 
Pakistani students and students from several Arab countries in 
the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

