<H3> <TI>   * Radio Communications Inaugurated in Chah Bahar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94LA0078E Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 29 Dec 93 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0078E </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Zahedan--IRNA. 3 Azar [21 December]--The Sistan va 
Baluchestan General Office of Ports and Shipping has opened a 
radio communications station in Chah Bahar with an advanced 
system. 
  This naval communications system can provide telegraph, 
telephone, and telex service between domestic and foreign 
representative offices, shipping companies and foreign ships in 
all the four naval districts designated by the International 
Maritime Organization. 
  At this station's inauguration ceremony, the executive 
director of the Ports and Shipping Organization gave a speech. 
He said: The Port of Chah Bahar is quite important as a transit 
area for goods moving between Afghanistan, Central Asia, and 
Iran. 
  He said the communications system created in this port is 
one 
of the most advanced maritime communications facilities in the 
world. He said: This system will be installed and put into 
operation within two months by domestic specialists and experts. 

</TEXT>

