<H3> <TI>   Abu-Nidal `Terrorists' Charged in Diplomat's Murder </TI></H3>
<H4>   Other Members Apprehended </H4>
<F P=102> JN2202151394 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 22-23 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2202151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] AKHIR KHABAR has learned that the security forces 
apprehended 30 members of Fatah-the Revolutionary Council [led 
by Abu Nidal] in Amman on Wednesday [16 February], and that 
'Abbas al-Qaysi and Fathi Abu-Salimah were among those 
apprehended. 
  The wife of one of those apprehended informed AKHIR KHABAR 
that the security forces had asked 'Abbas al-Qaysi, a 
Amman-based Fatah-Revolutionary Council leader and former 
prisoner, to report to them. Meanwhile, they searched his house 
and detained him, along with others, most of whom were veteran 
prisoners who spent many long years in jail. They had been 
freed in early 1990. 

</TEXT>

