Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat has left Amman 
after attending the signature of the Yemeni reconciliation and 
reform accord. 
  Mr. 'Arafat paid tribute to the efforts exerted by his 
majesty the king in bringing about the agreement between the 
parties of the political spectrum in Yemen. He described the 
signing of the accord as a historic and important incident that 
supported the pillars of the Yemeni unity. 
  He said the ratification of the accord by Yemeni President 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his deputy 'Ali Salim al-Bid is 
considered a beneficial action not only to Yemen but to the Arab 
nation as a whole. 

