<H3> <TI>   Al-Majali Briefs Cabinet on Yemeni Reconciliation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2202171494 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1600 GMT 
22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2202171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The cabinet held an ordinary session today under 
Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali. During the session, 
Dr. al-Majali presented a briefing on Jordan's pan-Arab role in 
the Yemeni reconciliation, which was crowned with the meeting of 
Yemeni leaders in Amman and the signing of the accord document 
by Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Yemeni Vice President 
'Ali Salim al-Bid, and all the leaders of the coalition and 
opposition parties. The document was drawn up by the Yemeni 
dialogue committee to end the political crisis in fraternal 
Yemen. 
  Dr. al-Majali said that the Yemenis' implementation of the 
document is aimed at leading Yemen to the shores of safety. He 
stressed that the Yemeni people are aware of this critical 
historic stage they are facing and that they will overcome it 
with success, God willing. [passage omitted] 

