<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Darawshah Comments on Goals of Syria Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2202154394 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 20 Feb 94 p 
p 1, 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2202154394 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] London, Damascus -- 'Abd-al-Wahhab Darawshah, 
Arab deputy in the Israeli Knesset and representative of the 
Arab Democratic Party, has stressed that a visit to Syria by a 
delegation headed by him is imminent. And that the aim is to 
condole Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad for the death of his son, 
Staff Major Basil al-Asad, who was tragically killed in an 
accident last month. He said that "contacts are under way to 
set a date for the visit and the place from which we are going 
to cross to Syria." 
  Darawshah told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT over the telephone from his 
office in al-Nasirah that the visit is expected to take place 
within the next few days. And that he prefers to cross into 
Syrian territory via the Golan Heights so that there would be no 
need to use passports. He expressed his confidence that "Syria 
will offer all capabilities to make this visit a success." 
[passage omitted] 
  Syrian sources have not confirmed whether the delegation is 
going to discuss matters concerning the peace process. However, 
they said that it may propose some views vis-a-vis peace. 
  As for Darawshah, he stressed that the visit is limited to 
offering condolences to President al-Asad, his family, and the 
Syrian people for Basil's death." [no opening quotemarks as 
published] He added: "We are not entrusted with any official 
tasks or with conveying any messages." He went on: "Raising 
any political issues depends on the host, who is the one to 
decide the meeting's program and contents." [passage omitted] 
  On the makeup of the delegation, which will comprise 30 
figures, Darawshah said that it will represent all Palestinian 
geographical, religious, literary, educational, political, and 
national sectors and groups in Israel." [no opening quotemarks 
as published] According to Darawshah, the delegation will 
include Knesset members 'Abd-al-Wahhab Darawshah and Talab 
al-Sani'. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

