<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   NRP: Arabs Establishing `Settlements' in Valley </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2102194994 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2102194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The NRP [National Religious Party] has demanded 
that the government apply Israeli sovereignty to the Jordan Rift 
Valley settlements and declare them a security zone outside all 
political arrangements. This NRP demand was presented during a 
tour of the valley today. According to them, Palestinians are 
establishing settlements in the valley so as to endanger the 
Jewish majority there. Our territories correspondent Amir Hay 
reports: 
  The amazing revelation made by NRP leaders in the course of 
their tour of the Jordan Rift Valley was that Arab settlements 
are being established without permits. About 500 people have 
recently settled down in improvised structures in the al-Jiftliq 
area, and several hundred other families squatted in the area, 
in the words of the Jewish residents, establishing three more 
such centers. They arrived mostly from the Tubas and Janin 
areas. [passage omitted] 
  In less than three days, the Arab residents managed to set 
up 
an improvised mosque on the site. Jordan Valley residents claim 
that a 20-percent rise in unauthorized Arab settlement has been 
registered since the PLO-Israeli Declaration of Principles was 
signed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

