<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Clash With `Terrorists' in al-Badari </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2302151994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1352 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2302151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, 23 Feb (MENA)--Security troops in Asyut this 
morning mounted a search campaign in the city of al-Badari. 
Various police departments from the Asyut Governorate took part 
in the operation. 
  While the security forces were performing their routine 
work, 
terrorist elements fired on them, wounding Major Majdi Sulayman 
Musa, First Lieutenant Yasir Kamal Ibrahim, and Lieutenant 
'Abd-al- Muhsin Husayn. Two terrorists, one of them known to be 
dangerous, were also wounded. The clashes between the 
terrorists and police also wounded three Central Security 
conscripts and two passers by, Fahd Muhammad Mahmud, a student, 
and Su'ad 'Ali Ahmad, a farmer. 
  The al-Badari prosecutor's office is investigating the 
incident. The search operations in the area for the remaining 
terrorist elements and outlaws are continuing. 

