<H3> <TI>   Paper Urges Lebanon To Control Hizballah Activity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2402081494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2252 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2402081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 23 Feb (MENA)--AL-AKHBAR urges the Lebanese 
Government to control the activities of Hizballah in southern 
Lebanon, especially in the part controlled by Israel, allegedly 
as its security zone. 
  The paper says in its editorial for 24 February: This, 
however, does not mean we are calling for stopping the activity 
of the Lebanese resistance, which is a legitimate act against 
any occupier. But resistance must stem from genuinely patriotic 
elements; it must not be left to groups with suspect objectives. 
  The paper says Hizballah is working on behalf of Iran, 
implementing its policies and receiving financing and arms from 
it. 
  The paper says Iran sponsors terrorist groups in a number of 
Arab and Islamic countries, and is trying to foil the peace 
talks between Israel and the Palestinians, Syrians, and Lebanese. 
  AL-AKHBAR concludes that imposing Lebanese Government 
control 
over Hizballah is an essential step that is in Lebanon's 
interest. 

