<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Confirms Knowledge of U.S. Envoy's Trip South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2302170594 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1900 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2302170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih has 
confirmed that the tour by Donald Petterson, the U.S ambassador 
in Khartoum, of some areas in the south of the country took 
place with the knowledge of the Foreign Ministry. He added that 
the American ambassador had briefed him during a meeting with 
him today about his tour of some areas on the southern border. 
Abu-Salih said that the government approved the food drops for 
camps of displaced people in the Mundri and (Parajok) areas in 
cooperation with the United Nations. Dr. Abu-Salih added that 
he had assured the American ambassador that the government was 
trying to end to the ongoing war in the south, stressing that 
Sudan was very dependent on the initiative of the 
Intergovernmental Authority on Drought and Development states. 
The foreign minister affirmed that a cease-fire in the south 
should be part of a comprehensive solution to the problem of the 
south. 

</TEXT>

