<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abu-Salih Urges Diplomatic Solution in South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2302120594 Omdurman National Unity Radio in Arabic 1315 
GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2302120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman National Unity Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Husayn Abu-Salih has confirmed 
Sudan's belief that the southern issue should be dealt with 
within the framework of a diplomatic solution. Commenting on 
the American ambassador to Sudan's remarks at his news 
conference in Nairobi, Husayn Abu-Salih said diplomatic efforts 
represent a priority for solving the problem of the south. He 
added: We will give our attention to the Intergovernmental 
Authority on Drought and Development initiative. He confirmed 
Sudan's support for a peaceful solution. 
  On the appointment of an American envoy to Sudan, Husayn 
Abu-Salih said that no official notification from the American 
Administration has reached Sudan in this connection. He 
expressed his hope for earnest and (?successful) cooperation to 
reach a peaceful, just, and rapid solution in order to end the 
bloodshed and the exhaustion of resources and to proceed towards 
development and stability. 

</TEXT>

