<H3> <TI>   Rabin on Timeline for Withdrawal, Final Accord </TI></H3>
<H4>   Three Months `Reasonable' for Accord </H4>
<F P=102> LD2302133794 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
1200 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Portuguese Prime Minister Silva 
spoke of bilateral relations, which in the last few years have 
enjoyed a significant boost. He noted that trade has increased 
by 30 percent. Silva went on to mention the negotiations 
between Israel and the European Union. He advocated an 
identical accord to that in force with the European Free Trade 
Association countries. 
  Prime Minister Rabin said he did not believe that the 
Israeli 
troop withdrawal from the Gaza Strip and Jericho would take 
place in the next two weeks as it had been reported. Rabin is 
optimistic but said the next three months was a more reasonable 
period for a final accord. 

</TEXT>

