<H3> <TI>   Rabin on Timeline for Withdrawal, Final Accord </TI></H3>
<H4>   Overall Settlement `Possible' in 1994 </H4>
<F P=102> LD2302224294 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302224294 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israel thinks it possible for a comprehensive 
agreement to be signed with the Arab states by the end of the 
year: This was stated this evening by Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin at a dinner with [Portuguese Prime Minister] Cavaco Silva 
and other members of the government, during which Rabin offered 
to extend the hand of peace. 
  [Begin recording of Rabin, in English] As for our other 
negotiating partners, my message is this: I am extending my hand 
to you as a sign of peace. We feel no hatred, no grudge or 
bigotry. Let us all make a pledge that we will do our utmost to 
achieve peace during this coming year so as to usher in a new 
era in a new Middle East, an era in which the integrity, the 
security and the sovereignty of all nations, all states, are 
respected in that Middle East of our wishes, where cooperation 
with dignity will prevail. [end recording] 
  A statement to go down in history, marking the high point of 
this first day of the Israeli Prime Minister's visit to Portugal. 

</TEXT>

