<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Intelligence Officers on Arab's Economic Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2102171894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 21 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2102171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] IDF [Israel Defense Forces] Intelligence Branch 
officers today told the Knesset Foreign Affairs and Defense 
Committee that the Arab countries are facing serious economic 
difficulties. This state of affairs is taking its affecting 
both the military procurement and the civilian population's 
living condition. 
  Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that the officers also 
briefed the Knesset members of an improvement in Syria's 
economic situation following a rise in the production of oil. 
The intelligence officers also believe that the economic aspect 
will play an important role in the Palestinian ability to set up 
a self-government. 

</TEXT>

