<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab Likud Members Deny Seeking 'Arafat Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2402102294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 24 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2402102294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Arab and Druze Likud activists have denied that 
they asked 'Arafat's aide Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi to arrange a visit 
in Tunis. They were reacting to Dr. al-Tibi's remarks that a 
delegation of Israeli Arab Likud supporters is not welcome in 
Tunis, and that 'Arafat is not interested in meeting them. Ayub 
Qara', a member of the Likud's secretariat, told our 
correspondent Yo'el Dar that it was Dr. al-Tibi who approached 
the Druze activists and asked them to hand him names of Likud 
supporters in key positions who would be willing to travel to 
Tunis and help promote the peace process. Qara' said that Arab 
members of the Likud Central Committee want to be a bridge to 
peace and contribute to the ongoing process. 

</TEXT>

