<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fugitive Caught in Gaza; Other Incidents Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2302184094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1800 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2302184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A border police undercover unit this evening 
captured an Islamic Jihad fugitive in Gaza city. The man was 
captured when he refused soldiers' orders to stop and tried to 
run over one of the soldiers with his car. 
  In Rafah, a Palestinian was shot by troops and moderately 
wounded. He was part of a group that ran away after refusing 
soldiers' orders to stop. 
  A border police unit in Bethlehem this afternoon discovered 
a 
bomb in Manger Square. The device was safely defused by a 
Border Police sapper. 
  A Tel Aviv Magistrates Court has extended the remand in 
custody by a week of a Ramla resident suspected of handing over 
an Uzi submachine gun to a resident of Rafah. The accused, who 
was also suspected of hiding other weapons near his home, denies 
the allegations. 
  A police officer has been shot near Dimona. He is now 
hospitalized at Soroka Hospital in Beersheba. His condition is 
described as light to moderate. The officer told investigators 
that while he was waiting at a bus stop, a car stopped alongside 
him and three Palestinians attempted to force him into the 
vehicle. He succeeded in fighting them off, but a third man 
shot him in the leg. Security forces are investigating. 

</TEXT>

