<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian, Israeli Delegations End Talks in Cairo </TI></H3>
<H4>   Palestinian Official: Talks `Fruitful' </H4>
<F P=102> JN2302190494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1530 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2302190494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Hasan 'Asfur, deputy head of the Palestinian </F>
delegation to the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks by Sa'id 
Mu'addi; in Cairo, Egypt; date not given; from the "With the 
Events" feature--recorded] 
  [Text] [Mu'addi] Mr. Hasan 'Asfur from Cairo: A joint 
statement was issued today after the end of negotiations between 
the Israeli and Palestinian delegations. What was the content 
of the statement? 
  ['Asfur] The statement refers to the nature of the 
atmosphere 
prevailing at the negotiations. The atmosphere was 
constructive, positive, and practical. The negotiations were 
fruitful, and we achieved progress on three issues; namely, 
civilian issues, security issues, and confidence building 
measures. In fact, we have achieved progress, and both sides 
are satisfied with it and hope it will open the way for major 
progress next week. 
  [Mu'addi] Mr. Hasan, what are the outstanding issues of 
disagreement? 
  ['Asfur] There are several issues over which we have not yet 
reached any agreement, including some security and civilian 
issues and confidence-building measures. We hope that next 
week's negotiations will achieve more progress on these issues. 
  [Mu'addi] What about the Palestinian police? Have you 
reached any agreement on it? 
  ['Asfur] No, we have not yet reached any agreement. The size 
of this police force and the type of weapons it will use are 
still under discussion. 
  [Mu'addi] What about efforts to release Palestinian 
prisoners? 
  ['Asfur] There is serious and continuing discussion of this 
issue, and I believe that matters are moving in the right 
direction. 
  [Mu'addi] Have there been contacts since the press statement 
about holding a summit meeting between Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin and PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat in Cairo next week? 
  ['Asfur] Negotiations will resume in Cairo next week on 
Israeli withdrawal from the Gaza Strip and Jericho area, and we 
hope a meeting will take place between President 'Arafat and 
Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin when both deem it necessary. 
  [Mu'addi] Do you believe that all issues will be discussed 
next week? 
  ['Asfur] It is difficult to fix such a date, but we believe 
that matters are moving in the right direction. We hope we will 
reach an agreement within a short time, before the blessed 'Id 
al-Fitr, that will please our people and both sides. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

