<H3> <TI>   `Stalemate' Reported in Paris Economic Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2402062194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 24 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2402062194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The economic talks between Israel and the PLO in 
Paris have run into a stalemate. In their meeting last night, 
Finance Minister Avraham Shohat and PLO representative 
Abu-al-'Ala' [Ahmad Quray'] failed to overcome the disagreements 
between the sides. Our correspondent Yo'av Tocker reports that 
the meeting lasted five hours ending without results. The main 
dispute concerns the issue of joint customs duties to be levied 
by Israel and the autonomy. 

</TEXT>

