<H3> <TI>   President, PRC Official Meet, Discuss Various Topics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2302150694 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2302150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The vice premier and foreign minister of China, Mr. 
Qian Qichen, called on President Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari at 
the Aiwan-i-Sadr [President House] today and exchanged views 
with him on various bilateral and regional issues. They 
expressed satisfaction at the depth and direction of bilateral 
relations between Pakistan and China. Reviewing various aspects 
of bilateral cooperation, they shared the desire to further 
expand it to mutual benefit. During the meeting, regional 
situation with particular reference to situation in occupied 
Kashmir and Afghanistan was considered in depth. Both the 
leaders underlined the need to immediately stop human rights 
violations in occupied Kashmir and resolve the issue peacefully 
and in accordance with the wishes of its people and 
international law. On Afghanistan, the need to restore peace 
was stressed from both the sides. It was felt that the 
continuing bloodshed was depriving the people of Afghanistan of 
the fruits of their victory in their struggle against foreign 
occupation. 

