<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministers Assail Pakistani `Support to Subversion' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2302100494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2302100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government will continue to urge Pakistan at 
every available opportunity to stop its support to subversion 
and terrorism directed against India. The minister of state for 
external affairs, Mr. R.L. Bhatia, informed the Rajya Sabha in a 
written reply that New Delhi has apprised the international 
community of Pakistan's role in these activities. He termed 
this approach by Pakistan as totally unacceptable and in 
violation of the Simla agreement and universally accepted norms 
of international conduct. 
  The Lok Sabha was told that there has been an increase in 
firings by the Pakistani troops at Indian posts in the Uri, 
Punch, and Rajaori sectors during the past few months. The 
minister of state for defense, Mr. Mallikarjun, told the house 
in a written reply that all such developments are carefully 
assessed and appropriate and timely steps taken. He told the 
members that our troops are fully prepared to meet any 
eventuality. 

