<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Resistance' Reports Anti-Israeli Operations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1902181294 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 19 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1902181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 'Ali Dawud from al-Nabatiyah] </F>
  [Text] Tension and anticipation still prevail in the 
liberated villages in the south in the wake of continued Israeli 
aggression, which was renewed today against villages in the 
central sector. The resistance retaliated with an operation 
against a joint patrol along the al-Qantarah-al-Tayyibah road 
this afternoon. 
  The Israeli occupation troops bombarded the hills of 
Qabrikhah, Tulin, al-Tamiriyah, Shaqra, and Wadi al-Saluqi with 
155-mm tank artillery and 120-mm mortars this afternoon. 
Citizen Hasan 'Ali 'Awali was wounded in Tulin and was taken to 
the Tibnin government hospital for treatment. 
  At 1500 today, agent Lahd [South Lebanese Army] positions in 
'Alman and al-Shumariyah bombarded the area surrounding the 
positions with 82-mm mortar fire. this was accompanied by 
machine-gun fire against adjacent forests. 
  According to reports from the occupied border strip, the 
occupation troops have arrested Salim 'Awadah, member of the al- 
Naqurah municipal council; his sons Hasan, Ibrahim, and 'Isam; 
and the latter's wife and took them to the al-Khiyam prison. 
  The Amal Movement and the Islamic Resistance announced in a 
joint statement that their forces attacked a joint patrol along 
the al- Qantarah-al-Tayyibah road at 1345 today. The statement 
said a vehicle was destroyed and its crew members were killed or 
wounded. Lahd's radio later reported the operation but kept 
silent on its losses. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

