<H3> <TI>   Hizballah's Qasim Denies Contacts To Stop Resistance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2002064894 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0545 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2002064894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hizballah Deputy Secretary General Na'im Qasim has 
denied reports that there have been contacts with Hizballah 
asking it to decrease its resistance operations. He asserted 
that no one asked them to cut down their operations during the 
Geneva summit. His party does not carry out resistance 
activities based on the negotiations, because "we do not believe 
in these negotiations," Shaykh Qasim said. He pointed out that 
resistance operations are escalated and reduced according to the 
objective situation on the ground, not according to political 
circumstances. 
  As for information coming from within Hizballah about 
preparations for a settlement, Shaykh Qasim clarified that the 
party opposes a settlement in the first place. He said: We are 
betting on its failure. We believe that there are enough 
complications and pressures to hamper many of the steps to a 
settlement. Therefore, Shaykh Qasim continued, the possibility 
of failure is as great as any other possibility. 

</TEXT>

