<F P=102>  JN2102205894 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2102205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News at Ten" program] </F>
  [Text] Jordan and the United States today signed an 
agreement under which the United States will finance a Jordanian 
purchase of 100,000 tonnes of U.S. wheat at a cost of $15 
million. The agreement was signed by Finance Minister Sami 
Qammuh and U.S. Charge d'Affaires Douglas Keene. 
  Mr. Qammuh said the loan will carry 2 percent annual 
interest 
for the first seven years and 3 percent thereafter. He said the 
loan was repayable in 24 installments beginning in the seventh 
year. Mr. Qammuh said 60 percent of the value of the loan was a 
grant from the United States to shore up Jordan's budget. 
  The U.S. charge d'affaires said the loan was one aspect of 
Jordanian-U.S. cooperation. 

