<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Clash Events; Efforts To End Conflict </TI></H3>
<H4>   Council of Ministers Notes Situation </H4>
<F P=102> JN2302180594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2302180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Ministers held its periodic meeting 
this afternoon under the chairmanship of First Deputy Prime 
Minister brother Dr. Hasan Makki. After reviewing the decisions 
it made during its previous meetings, the council discussed 
topics on its agenda and was briefed by the interior minister on 
the security situation in the country. 
  The interior minister cited the need to promote the 
ministry's efforts to maintain general security, stability, and 
peace of mind in the society. He also stressed that the 
ministry would exert every effort to prevent anything that 
disturbs security and stability. The council also discussed 
several issues listed on its agenda and adopted suitable 
decisions and measures. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

