<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Clash Events; Efforts To End Conflict </TI></H3>
<H4>   Troops Ordered Back to Barracks </H4>
<F P=102> JN2302201694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1900 GMT 
23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2302201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih has ordered Defense 
Minister Haytham Qasim Tahir to return the southern troops 
deployed in the Abyan area, east of Aden, to their barracks in 
Hadhramaut in the east. In a message to the defense minister, 
President Salih ordered his defense minister to ban armed 
flights without a prior agreement with the chief of staff and 
the higher commander of the Yemeni Armed Forces. 
  In his message, the Yemeni president stressed that moving a 
military unit from one place to another without a regular 
approval by the higher commander of the Armed Forces constitutes 
a violation of the Constitution and the document of accord, 
which was signed in Amman last Sunday to end the political 
crisis in the country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

