<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian, Israeli Delegations End Talks in Cairo </TI></H3>
<H4>   Shahaq, Sha'th Express Satisfaction </H4>
<F P=102> TA2302165594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2302165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The talks between the Israeli and Palestinian 
delegations in Cairo have ended. Amnon Shahaq and Nabil Sha'th, 
heads of the two delegations, expressed satisfaction with the 
progress made in the current round of talks and expect further 
progress to be made when they meet again in Cairo next week. 
  Our correspondent Karmela Menashe reports the delegations 
discussed three main issues: security problems, the transfer of 
civilian powers, and what is known as confidence-building 
measures such as the release of prisoners. The delegations also 
discussed the preparations for and the size of the Palestinian 
police force. The Civilian Affairs Committee discussed 
archaeological issues, the electronic media, and land and 
population registration. 

</TEXT>

