<H3> <TI>   Second Five-Year Plan Direction in Sectors </TI></H3>
<H4>   Education in Ministry of Mines, Metals </H4>
<F P=102> 94LA0079C Tehran RESALAT in Persian 29 Dec 93 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0079C </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran RESALAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Tehran, (IRNA) -- At the closing ceremonies for the 
Second Exhibition of Photographs of Geological and Mining 
Phenomena, the minister of mines and metals said: More than 15 
billion rials has been allocated to raise the educational level 
of this ministry's personnel in the area of mines and metals. 
  Engineer Hoseyn Mahluji said: In the area of training in the 
Second Five-Year Plan, this ministry will spend twice as much on 
the aggregate under its authority. 
  He said: The Ministry of Mines and Metals is prepared to 
assist any college or university that is active teaching in the 
mines and metals sector, and it will place the resources of the 
organizations under its authority at the disposal of these 
institutions. 
  This exhibition, which opened on 27 Azar [18 December], 
closed on Sunday with the presentation of prizes to the 
photographers who took the 10 best pictures. 

</TEXT>

