  [Text] Pakistan is considering closing down its embassy 
temporarily in Kabul following yesterday's incident there. Law 
Minister Syed Iqbal Haider in a statement in the Senate today 
assured the members that a decision in this regard would be made 
after reviewing all aspects of Pakistan's relations with 
Afghanistan. He expressed the government's resolve that 
criminal activities will not be allowed to affect the close 
brotherly relations between the two countries. The law minister 
told the house that Pakistani foreign minister, Sardar Asif 
Ahmad Ali, who is in Kabul, raised the issue to Commander Ahmad 
Shah Mas'ud, who is holding military control over Kabul. Mas'ud 
expressed regret over the incident and inspected the embassy 
along with the foreign minister at midnight last night. 

