<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Dangerous' `RAW' Agent Arrested Near Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2402130694 Karachi NAWA-I-WAQT in Urdu 16 Feb 94 pp 8, 7 </F>
<F P=103> BK2402130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Karachi NAWA-I-WAQT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dhirke -- A dangerous agent of the Indian terrorist 
organization, "Research and Analysis Wing [RAW]," was arrested 
as soon as he crossed over into Pakistani territory. It has 
been learned that Lakshman Das, a dangerous "RAW" agent, was 
arrested by a Pakistani secret investigation agency when he was 
entering Pakistani territory near Dhirke from India's Jaisalmer 
area. A large amount of Indian currency and some important 
documents have been recovered from the arrested terrorist. It 
has also been learned that Lakshman Das was coming to Pakistan 
after receiving training at a RAW camp in India's Bhilwara 
District to carry out terroristic activities in Sindh Province. 
During the interrogation, he identified certain important 
personalities of Pakistan, especially an influential Hindu 
businessmen from Sindh Province, who provided assistance, 
Pakistani currency, and arms to RAW agents to carry out acts of 
terrorism inside Pakistan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

