<F P=102>  94LA0081F Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 2 Feb 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0081F </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Tehran, 6 Bahman [26 Jan] (IRNA) -- The 
Embassy of the Republic of Kazakhstan was officially opened in 
Tehran with the raising of the flag of that country in the 
presence of the ministers of foreign affairs of Iran and 
Kazakhstan. 
  Tuleutai Suleymenov, the Kazakhstani minister of foreign 
affairs, said during the embassy inauguration ceremonies, which 
were also attended by several foreign ministers of other Asian 
republics: With the opening of the Kazakhstan Embassy in Iran, 
mutual relations between the two countries in political, 
cultural, commercial, and economic areas will be actively 
expanded. 
  Dr. 'Ali Akbar Velayati also termed the inauguration of the 
Kazakhstan Embassy in Iran one of the fruits of the friendly 
relations between that country and the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  It is interesting that Myrzadai Zholdasbekov, the 
Kazakhstani 
Ambassador, submitted his credentials to President Hojjat 
ol-Eslam Hashemi-Rafsanjani last Azar 2 [23 November]. 

</TEXT>

