<H3> <TI>   * Maragheh's Sahand Airport Operational </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94LA0081B Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 19 Jan 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0081B </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [First paragraph is KEYHAN-E HAVA'I introduction] </F>
  [Text] Tabriz, 21 Dey [11 Jan] (IRNA) -- The 
40,000-telephone center of Maragheh has become operational. 
On the occasion of the anniversary of the prophethood of the 
revered prophet of Islam, the "Sahand" Airport of the city of 
Maragheh became operational. 
  During these ceremonies, in which the ministers of roads and 
transport, energy, and post, telegraph and telephone also 
participated, it was announced that the Maragheh Sahand Airport 
was built with 1.6 billion rials provided by the people. 
  This airport, with a 3-km airstrip, is capable of handling 
small passenger airplanes. 
  With the operation of this airport, the Maragheh-Tehran air 
route, with two flights per week, will soon be established. 
  At the same time, the 40,000-telephone center of the city of 
Maragheh was also inaugurated this week. 
  With the operation of this center, the number of telephones 
in Maragheh increased from 8,000 to 40,000. 
  This center is the first completely digital telephone center 
in Eastern Azarbaijan. 

</TEXT>

