<F P=100> ARAB-ISRAELI TALKS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Issues Left for 'Arafat, Rabin To Resolve </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2402184794 Cairo ESC Television in Arabic 1800 GMT 24 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2402184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo ESC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian sources have stated that the Palestinian 
and Israeli negotiators, who concluded their talks in Cairo 
today on self-rule for the Palestinians in Gaza and Jericho, 
agreed to leave four topics relating to security and civilian 
services to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli 
Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin to solve. 
  The topics include Palestinian passports and postal stamps, 
the size of the Palestinian police force, and the area of 
Jericho to enjoy self-rule under the agreement. The same 
sources added that the Israelis refuse to take any step that may 
give the self-rule areas the form of a state, such as the 
issuing of passports and postal stamps. 
  PLO sources have noted that Israeli troops have begun to 
withdraw from some sites in Gaza and Jericho in preparation for 
the final withdrawal from the two regions. Five Palestinian 
police officers have arrived in Gaza and Jericho to discuss how 
the Palestinian police force will be deployed once the Israeli 
withdrawal is finalized. 

</TEXT>

