<F P=100> ARAB-ISRAELI TALKS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Tarifi Interviewed on Committee Meeting in Cairo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2302132894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1050 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2302132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Jamil al-Tarifi, head of the Palestinian </F>
side to the Palestinian-Israeli Civil Affairs Committee, by 
Sa'id Mu'addi, in Cairo, date not given; from the "With the 
Midday Events" program--recorded] 
  [Text] [Mu'addi] What stage has been reached in your 
discussion of the subject of transferring civil powers to the 
Palestinians? 
  [Al-Tarifi] In my opinion, diplomatic relations reached a 
very advanced stage. Yesterday, we concluded our discussion of 
the issue of agreement on the lands of both state and absentees. 
God willing, we will reach agreement on the issue of 
communications today. Two subjects, that is, organization and 
planning, and water, will be discussed next week. There is also 
the subject of jurisdictions, which is now being discussed in 
Paris as it is linked to the economic committee there. 
  [Mu'addi] Regarding the subject of visas, land registration, 
and water resources, has an understanding or agreement been 
reached on these topics? 
  [Al-Tarifi] Regarding visas, yes there is an agreement. The 
subject of water resources will be discussed next week, God 
willing. 
  [Mu'addi] Can we then say that next week will witness the 
end 
of negotiations within the framework of the Civilian Affairs 
Committee and that powers can be transferred to the Palestinians? 
  [Al-Tarifi] I hope so, God willing. 
  [Mu'addi] Has the Palestinian side made preparations and 
formed special cadres to take civil authority over from the 
civil administration? 
  [Al-Tarifi] In my opinion, and you know this, brother Sa'id, 
all present departments are currently run by Palestinians. Very 
few Israeli officials are present. We have qualified 
Palestinian cadres and we can assume power immediately. 

</TEXT>

