<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunman Kills Over 50 Arabs at Hebron Mosque 25 Feb </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Rebels Movement' Assumes Responsibility </H4>
<F P=102> TA2502070894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0658 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2502070894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A previously unknown movement, the Rebels Movement 
[Tnu'at Hamordim], an extreme Jewish movement whose members 
apparently belong to or are affiliated in some way with the Kakh 
Movement, called IDF Radio's news studio a short time ago and 
assumed responsibility for the massacre in Hebron. The 
anonymous caller said that the Rebels Movement assumes 
responsibility for the massacre committed to avenge the slaying 
of Rabbi Me'ir Kahana, the late leader of the Kakh Movement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

